    p.bx--type-p.u-pb-4
      | The position of tooltips is flexible and will change depending on how close the element is to the edge of the screen. Use tooltips to identify or add a small amount of information to an element.

    p.bx--type-p
      | Typically, tooltips are used to help users understand the meaning or purpose of icons, parts of a chart and other info details, showing the full version of truncated text, value of a concrete part of some visualization dashboard, or displaying the alt text for an image. LUCA tooltips replace standard browser tooltips when more emphasis is required. Not be used to communicate error messages or important account information.

